One for the HYDA  index for Nov 8:

At 8:15 last night, after a day of what surely was the lowest point in my Enron journey, I went home.  Upon arrival, an old black dog was hit by a car that sped away.  The dog died at 9:00 on my doorstop.  We helped our neighbors bury him.  Lets hope the crows know something different for today's report.

Oh, Nov 8th was also my husband's birthday.  Obviously no party.

Elizabeth Sager
